	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="Wonderful subtext for “I want to” statements.

Fully agree and hold the same intention for this sort of thing. 

There is a difference between wanting something and committing to doing it. 

Subtle but important. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/askyatharth/status/1412320015152336896&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 23:01:42 GMT" tweetId="1412547331992457219" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412547331992457219" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Plant seeds liberally and enthusiastically; tend to them when inspired to do so." type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 23:02:35 GMT" tweetId="1412547556140326912" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412547556140326912" inReplyToId="1412547331992457219" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I’m getting a lot of Twitter “Topics” on my feed all of a sudden. 

Anyone else? How do I make them go away?" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:46:00 GMT" tweetId="1412422585971773447" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1412422585971773447" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="Paper is awesome. Tools for thought still have a long way to go to catch paper." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:17:40 GMT" tweetId="1411735979455565828" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411735979455565828" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Making outlines, maps, lists — drawing lines — new drafts — spreading them all out over the table." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:20:07 GMT" tweetId="1411736594491510787" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411736594491510787" inReplyToId="1411735979455565828" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="An AR environment I’d like would simply replicate the ability to write stuff on a tablet, then spread them out into my physical surroundings." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:23:57 GMT" tweetId="1411737557788995587" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411737557788995587" inReplyToId="1411736594491510787" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
							<outline text="And also better paper → electronic conversion workflows.

Lists, maps, outlines, doodles into their electronic equivalent. 

Paper as the cutting edge, electronics as the full framework and repository." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:26:07 GMT" tweetId="1411738105816748034" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411738105816748034" inReplyToId="1411737557788995587" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
								<outline text="Then I’d like to choose pieces of my full repository to doodle and play with — with the full expression range and freedom of paper.

Like clicking into a node and just exploring thoughts in whatever form feels right.

Then compressing that exploration into electronic edits." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:33:17 GMT" tweetId="1411739909430419465" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411739909430419465" inReplyToId="1411738105816748034" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
									<outline text="Paper isn’t always the right tool, of course. It has clear limitations. 

But wow does it ever feel freeing." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 17:35:21 GMT" tweetId="1411740429326901251" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1411740429326901251" inReplyToId="1411739909430419465" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="This might be my new favourite music-related question.

The answers are great for discovery and the reflective process is great for rediscovery. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/noahpinion/status/1410786720459657219&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 03:01:02 GMT" tweetId="1410795623939444736" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1410795623939444736" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				<outline text="This is absolutely wild. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/alexandernl/status/1410253599502962692&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 19:06:47 GMT" tweetId="1410676275673538562" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1410676275673538562" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 25" type="calendarDay" name="25" >
				<outline text="Language compresses the true experience of reality. https://t.co/ggyYK8RFvm" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 11:40:49 GMT" tweetId="1408389715187884032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408389715187884032" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Precise speech helps to minimize the lossiness of communication." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 11:44:39 GMT" tweetId="1408390679403896835" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408390679403896835" inReplyToId="1408389715187884032" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="You’re still pointing at something — but you’re at least using a better pointer." type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 12:09:24 GMT" tweetId="1408396910096945157" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408396910096945157" inReplyToId="1408390679403896835" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 24" type="calendarDay" name="24" >
				<outline text="I’m tired of training Google visual recognition algorithms with reCAPTCHA." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 21:11:53 GMT" tweetId="1408171041436938243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408171041436938243" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Is there not another way to prove my human-ness?" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 21:12:42 GMT" tweetId="1408171245187776513" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408171245187776513" inReplyToId="1408171041436938243" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I enjoy meme formats as much as I enjoy memes." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:31:30 GMT" tweetId="1408100479423455240" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408100479423455240" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="Meta-memes" type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:32:04 GMT" tweetId="1408100622516338692" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408100622516338692" inReplyToId="1408100479423455240" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Deleted tweets should flatten as an image when quote-tweeted by others." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:26:03 GMT" tweetId="1408099109819518977" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099109819518977" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
					<outline text="As in, if a tweet is deleted once its quote-tweeted — it should exist in the quoted context as a flattened copy." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:26:46 GMT" tweetId="1408099288819900426" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099288819900426" inReplyToId="1408099109819518977" tweetUserName="brandontoner" >
						<outline text="Otherwise it sets up some brutal house-of-cards shit." type="tweet" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2021 16:27:12 GMT" tweetId="1408099400413585413" urltweet="https://twitter.com/brandontoner/status/1408099400413585413" inReplyToId="1408099288819900426" tweetUserName="brandontoner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			</outline>
		</body>
